node.tooltip: Click to edit the XTAL frequency.
PLL output frequency must be between 24 MHz and 64 MHz.
The system clock (ICLK) is used as the operating clock of the CPU, DMAC, DTC, ROM and RAM. \nMaximum frequency is 48 MHz.
The Peripheral clock A (PCLKA) is used as the operating clock for the SPI, SCI, SCE5, CRC and GPT (bus clock) modules. \nMaximum frequency is 48 MHz.
The Peripheral clock B (PCLKB) is used as the operating clock for all other modules not supported by PCLKA, PCLKC and PCLKD. \nMaximum frequency is 32 MHz.
The Peripheral clock C (PCLKC) is used as the operating clock for the ADC module. \nMaximum frequency is 64 MHz.
The Peripheral clock D (PCLKD) is used as the operating clock for the GPT (count clock) module. \nMaximum frequency is 64 MHz.

The flash-interface clock (FCLK) is used as the operating clock for the flash-memory interfaces.\nThat is, FCLK is used for programming and erasure of the ROM and E2 DataFlash, and reading from the E2 DataFlash. \nFrequency must be between 1 Hz and 32 MHz when any of these operations are used.
Frequency output on the CLKOUT pin if CLKOUT is enabled. \nMaximum frequency is 16 MHz.
